track_notes:
A route completed by Terry G0VWP in April 2014 and submitted on his behalf. I used Terrys route to good effect on 26 Oct 2018. It is perfect. I parked just before the cottage in the lane - plenty of width in the track there. If you need more info look at my blog Catterblog - find on google. 

73 de Phil
This is the middle summit of a round trip of -128 -145 and -143. It took me about 10 hours including activations. There was about 4.5 hours walking time.
